These observational sites spanned a large geographical area (120 - 124 °W, 35.2 - 39.7 °N) and climate gradient (12.8 - 17 °C temperature, 255 - 1840 mm precipitation).

These observational sites spanned an approximately 30,000 km2 geographical area.

Overall, the 12 observational sites had significant warming (0.0177 °C yr-1) and significant drying (4.22 mm yr-1) over the years.

By site, 7 out of the 12 sites had significant warming and 1 had significant drying over the years. Among all 12 sites, the warming rate ranged from 0.00531 °C yr-1 to 0.0278 °C yr-1; the drying rate ranged from -0.0278 mm yr-1 to 15.1 mm yr-1.

The experiment occupied ~0.75 ha within a 5-ha grassland stand and experienced a large variation of plot-level temperature (8.69 - 12.3 °C) and precipitation (240 - 1380 mm) in 2174 total plot years.
